            </li>
<li>
	      
<p><strong>Hydrogen bromide with postassium hydroxide</strong></p>

              
<p>Hydrogen bromide reacts with potassium hydroxide to form potassium bromide (the salt) and water. Potassium bromide is made up of  \(\text{K}^{+}\) cations from the base \((\text{KOH})\) and \(\text{Br}^{-}\) anions from the acid \((\text{HBr})\).</p>

	      
