            </li>
<li>
	      
<p><strong>Hydrochloric acid with sodium hydrocarbonate</strong></p>

              
<p>Hydrochloric acid reacts with sodium hydrocarbonate to form sodium chloride (the salt), water and carbon dioxide. Sodium chloride is made up of  \(\text{Na}^{+}\) cations from the base \((\text{NaHCO}_{3})\) and  \(\text{Cl}^{-}\) anions from the acid \((\text{HCl})\).</p>

              
